    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The society led a 2009 restoration of the Salisbury Center Covered Bridge, a rare Spruce Creek span.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19,
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://museumsdatabase.com/museums/view/22045"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Salisbury Center was named after Salisbury, Connecticut, where many early settlers had lived.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://herkimer.nygenweb.net/salisbury.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "On Spruce Creek, Salisbury Center once hosted two churches, a hotel, two stores, mills, a peg factory, and about 300 residents.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
